Complex Data Analysis Project¶

Analysis of the Amazon dataset of co-purchased products from March 02 2003

Initial Network¶

In [210]:
G = nx.read_edgelist('Amazon0302.txt', delimiter='\t', create_using=nx.DiGraph(), nodetype=int, comments='#')

print("Characteristics of the initial graph:")
print("Name: Amazon Co-Purchased Items in March 02 2003")
print("Number of Nodes: %d" % nx.number_of_nodes(G))
print("Number of Edges: %d" % nx.number_of_edges(G))

Number of Nodes: 262111
Number of Edges: 1234877

Subset Creation¶

The subset will be generated randomly, having 10% of the original nodes

In [202]:
num_nodes = int(0.1 * nx.number_of_nodes(G))
random.seed(13)
random_nodes = random.sample(list(G.nodes()), num_nodes)
subset = G.subgraph(random_nodes)

Removal of zero-degree nodes¶

In [204]:
nodes_degree = nx.degree(subset)
nodes_degree = dict(nodes_degree)
zero_degree = 0
for node in nodes_degree:
    if nodes_degree[node] == 0:
        zero_degree += 1
print(f"Number of nodes with degree 0: {zero_degree}")

nodes_to_remove = [node for node, degree in nodes_degree.items() if degree == 0]
subset = subset.copy()
subset.remove_nodes_from(nodes_to_remove)

Number of nodes with degree 0: 13410

In [191]:
mutable_subset_copy1 = subset.copy()
num_strongly_connected_components = []
impactful_nodes = []
x = 5000

for i in range(x):
    mutable_subset_copy1.remove_node(sorted_nodes[i])
    num_strongly_connected_components.append(nx.number_strongly_connected_components(mutable_subset_copy1))
    # print(f"Node {sorted_nodes[i]} removed with betweenness centrality {betweenness[sorted_nodes[i]]}")

    if i > 0 and num_strongly_connected_components[i] > num_strongly_connected_components[i - 1]:
        impactful_nodes.append(sorted_nodes[i])

In [199]:
nodes_communities = []
for node in sorted_nodes[:10]:
    for i, community in enumerate(communities_sorted):
        if node in community:
            nodes_communities.append((node, i + 1))
            break

for node, community_index in nodes_communities:
    print(f"Node {node} is in community {community_index}")

num_plots = len(nodes_communities)
num_cols = 2
num_rows = (num_plots + num_cols - 1) // num_cols

fig, axes = plt.subplots(num_rows, num_cols, figsize=(15, num_rows * 5))

axes = axes.flatten()

community_graphs = [subset.subgraph(communities_sorted[i - 1]).copy() for _, i in nodes_communities]
community_layouts = [nx.spring_layout(graph) for graph in community_graphs]

for i, (node, community_index) in enumerate(nodes_communities):
    ax = axes[i]
    community_graph = community_graphs[i]
    pos = community_layouts[i]
    nx.draw_networkx(community_graph, pos=pos, with_labels=False, node_color='lightblue', edge_color='gray', node_size=70, ax=ax)
    if node in community_graph:
        nx.draw_networkx_nodes(community_graph, pos=pos, nodelist=[node], node_color='red', node_size=70, ax=ax)
    ax.set_title(f"Community {community_index} with Node {node} Colored in Red")

for j in range(i + 1, len(axes)):
    fig.delaxes(axes[j])

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()

Paths Between Communities (Girvan)¶

In [200]:
paths_between_communities = []

for i in range(len(communities_sorted)):
    for j in range(i + 1, len(communities_sorted)):
        community1 = communities_sorted[i]
        community2 = communities_sorted[j]
        
        path_exists = False
        for node1 in community1:
            for node2 in community2:
                if nx.has_path(subset, node1, node2):
                    path_exists = True
                    break
            if path_exists:
                break
        
        if path_exists:
            print(f"Path exists between Community {i + 1} and Community {j + 1}")
            paths_between_communities.append((i + 1, j + 1))

# Print the communities that have a path between them
if paths_between_communities:
    print("Communities with a path between them:")
    for community1, community2 in paths_between_communities:
        print(f"Community {community1} and Community {community2}")
else:
    print("There are no paths between communities on the subset")

There are no paths between communities on the subset
